HEADWORD: Bullirag
<hw>Bul"li*rag</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<ets>bully</ets>,<pos>n. & v.</pos>, and <ets>rag</ets> to scold, rail.
Cf. <er>Ballarag</er>.]</ety> <def>To intimidate by bullying; to rally
contemptuously; to badger.</def> <mark>[Low]</mark>⟦br⟧
